column5: Thought I'd take a sec and show you one that may or may not soon be complete.  The foto could be better--just a quickie  Maybe i should paint a barrel on the creek bottom and call it Bronte
beautiful, you my friend have awsome talent
Thanks L---if I can't go catch em---might as well paint em
Well, maybe you don't have to be a steelheader to view it but a steelheader will surely appreciate it even more!  Just beautuful Bushart!
Thanks Guys  Has anyone caught my slip bobber?
If it was bronte it would be a shopping cart or a roll of orange snow fence Nice work
I do believe they call it a "float" now Terrance.Just saying.LOL  Looking forward to the finish as always.

sweet work bud, nicely done, u forgot  about the trolling spoons and, marshmellows and trebs to call it bronte lol, ya we call them flots now, bobbers are piece of crappy plastic with springs and hooks
I guess I'm just using that term from my walleye fishing where we called it a slip bobber rig
Looking good Terry I ain't steelheader but that float sure caught my attention Jacques
